1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:01,266
hello everyone

2
00:00:01,266 --> 00:00:04,666
today we are going to start our journey on TerraFirmGreg

3
00:00:04,666 --> 00:00:06,666
as the name suggests

4
00:00:06,666 --> 00:00:10,200

this is a modpack focused around Terrafirma and gregtech


5
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:12,633
but it also has a lot of create in it

6
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:14,266
as a Terraform pack

7
00:00:14,266 --> 00:00:17,100
the world generation is completely customized

8
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,966
and there are a lot of things we should worry about

9
00:00:20,033 --> 00:00:21,833
the first one is food

10
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:26,300
while it is easy to find it also has an expiration date

11
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:29,366
also we can't keep eating the same thing

12
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,500
we have to keep our diet balanced

13
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,500
to avoid running into issues

14
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:39,400
and we must also remember to drink some fluids if we do not want to pass out due to dehydration

15
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:39,800
finally

16
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:44,300
one other thing we have to keep track of is temperature and seasons

17
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:47,366
and since we spawned in a rather cold climate

18
00:00:47,366 --> 00:00:51,433
we shall start our journey by migrating towards a more warm climate

19
00:00:51,433 --> 00:00:53,666
so we start heading towards South

20
00:00:53,666 --> 00:00:55,500
and while we do so

21
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:57,866
we shall also get prepared for the night

22
00:00:57,866 --> 00:00:59,900
there won't be any weird creatures

23
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:01,433
but it will be quite dark

24
00:01:01,433 --> 00:01:06,333
so we gather some sticks and polish them into a kit to start fires

25
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,300
then we make sure it works

26
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:11,433
but a random wildfire won't be much useful

27
00:01:11,433 --> 00:01:14,666
so we start working on some tools to help us

28
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:18,433
we nap some of the rocks we gathered earlier on onto an axe head

29
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:20,366
which we attach to a broom

30
00:01:20,433 --> 00:01:21,966
now that we have an axe

31
00:01:21,966 --> 00:01:25,066
we can chop down the tree to gather some proper lumber

32
00:01:25,066 --> 00:01:29,000
but doing so on a huge tree is going to take a lot of time

33
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,833
so we instead look around for an already fallen and dry tree

34
00:01:33,033 --> 00:01:35,066
and this old tree is now so rotten

35
00:01:35,066 --> 00:01:38,100
that it basically chops down itself on its own

36
00:01:38,233 --> 00:01:39,066
with that lumber

37
00:01:39,066 --> 00:01:42,233
we can now try to start a proper controlled fire

38
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,400
we must also add a couple of twigs

39
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,300
to help the fire catch on

40
00:01:46,433 --> 00:01:47,633
and even then

41
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:51,100
we still have to try a couple of times to get the fire up

42
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:53,433
now that we have a proper managed fire

43
00:01:53,433 --> 00:01:56,600
we can use it to slowly ignite the tip of some sticks

44
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:58,033
making torches

45
00:01:58,066 --> 00:01:59,066
and with those

46
00:01:59,066 --> 00:02:03,466
we can now keep going on our journey even during the darkest nights

47
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:20,500
and after a couple of days of walking

48
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:24,866
we found ourselves stuck on an island surrounded only by the ocean

49
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,166
and while we managed to find a better climate

50
00:02:28,166 --> 00:02:31,366
this place isn't too good for setting up our settlement

51
00:02:31,533 --> 00:02:34,233
so we are going to walk back a little bit

52
00:02:34,233 --> 00:02:36,000
where the climate isn't too harsh

53
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,666
but the flora is great

54
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:40,900
now that we have found a nice place for our settlement

55
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:44,600
we have to find a nice place for all of the junk in our inventory

56
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,433
to do so

57
00:02:45,433 --> 00:02:49,166
we start by gathering some clay by a Riverside

58
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,333
and in this pack

59
00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:52,800
clay doesn't simply fall like sand

60
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:56,400
it even falls sideways when you move stuff close to it

61
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:59,433
anyways to speed up our gathering process

62
00:02:59,433 --> 00:03:01,266
we are going to nap some stones

63
00:03:01,266 --> 00:03:03,066
to make a rudimentary shovel

64
00:03:03,066 --> 00:03:04,500
once we have enough

65
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:08,400
we can spend the night molding the clay into all kinds of shapes

66
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,600
and as you can probably tell

67
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:14,633
the thing we need the most right now is a vessel to store some items

68
00:03:14,633 --> 00:03:17,633
but a clay vessel is too soft to be used

69
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,566
to harden it into ceramic

70
00:03:19,566 --> 00:03:21,633
we put it in a hole in the ground

71
00:03:21,633 --> 00:03:23,766
cover it with straw, some logs

72
00:03:23,766 --> 00:03:24,766
and fire it up

73
00:03:24,766 --> 00:03:27,000
the process will take 8 minutes

74
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,800
and we probably shouldn't have started it close to burnable stuff

75
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,400
the rain can't put off the pottery process

76
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:36,333
but it may helps us without mistake

77
00:03:36,333 --> 00:03:36,766
maybe

78
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,400
and while we wait for our pottery to be done

79
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:42,166
we can prepare some more for the next task

80
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,233
moulding metal

81
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:48,433
thus we prepare clay moulds for the main tools we will want to be made out of bronze

82
00:03:48,566 --> 00:03:49,800
and once again

83
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:53,033
we bury those in a hole in the ground under burnable stuff

84
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:55,233
then we pitch everything on fire

85
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:57,800
and we start making even more molds

86
00:03:57,800 --> 00:04:00,000
and while those are ceramifying

87
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:03,666
we can start scouting around our base for metal rich pebbles

88
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:06,833
we mainly look for tin and copper rich stones

89
00:04:06,833 --> 00:04:08,366
after collecting some

90
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,600
we go back home

91
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:11,566
where our first vessel is now ready

92
00:04:11,566 --> 00:04:14,766
and can finally help us free up some of our inventory

93
00:04:14,866 --> 00:04:16,833
and one nice feature is that

94
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:18,066
if we close the lid

95
00:04:18,066 --> 00:04:20,766
it will double the food preservation time

96
00:04:21,033 --> 00:04:24,100
next we take out of the Kiln our smaller vessels

97
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:26,900
those can be used as small backpacks

98
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:29,100
but the main use is melting metals

99
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:32,700
we could just melt some tetrahedrite to get some copper

100
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,366
but we want bronze

101
00:04:34,366 --> 00:04:34,933
to get it

102
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:37,500
we have to melt it with some cassiterite

103
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:39,366
the ratio is not strict

104
00:04:39,366 --> 00:04:42,900
so we can just go with something in the working range

105
00:04:43,066 --> 00:04:49,033
and we can see if it works and how much we get just by hovering over the vessel after filling it with rocks

106
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:50,200
once satisfied

107
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,800
we fire it up to melt the metals

108
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:55,633
then as soon as the fires goes out

109
00:04:55,633 --> 00:04:59,433
we retrieve it while it's still hot enough for the metal to be molten

110
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:02,433
and the first thing we want to use it for is a saw

111
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:05,000
we also manage to make a prospector pickaxe

112
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,600
and a normal pickaxe

113
00:05:06,666 --> 00:05:08,833
once the metal cooled down

114
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:10,366
we take it out of its molds

115
00:05:10,366 --> 00:05:13,033
and use it to craft an usable tool

116
00:05:13,100 --> 00:05:17,100
then we use our new saw to cut some lumber out of the logs we have

117
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:20,400
which we work into a crafting table and a proper chest

118
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:22,400
and now that I look at those

119
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:25,066
I think we couldn't have picked a worse looking wood

120
00:05:25,066 --> 00:05:28,100
so we recraft everything with a better looking one

121
00:05:28,133 --> 00:05:29,866
but to continue our adventure

122
00:05:29,866 --> 00:05:31,266
we will need more metal

123
00:05:31,266 --> 00:05:34,033
and the pebbles on the surface do not suffice

124
00:05:34,033 --> 00:05:35,866
to find bigger deposits of metal

125
00:05:35,866 --> 00:05:41,200
we use prospector pick by metal rich pebbles to locate surface ore deposits

126
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,933
once we locate some

127
00:05:42,933 --> 00:05:45,166
we start digging towards it

128
00:05:45,433 --> 00:05:47,033
but this is Terra firma

129
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:50,633
so even digging a tunnel is not as easy as you'd hope

130
00:05:50,766 --> 00:05:52,300
if we are not careful

131
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:54,500
even solid rock can fall on us

132
00:05:54,666 --> 00:05:55,900
to prevent that

133
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,633
we need support beams

134
00:05:57,633 --> 00:06:00,866
each one will safeguard the nearby rocks from falling

135
00:06:00,866 --> 00:06:04,366
and we have to build one every fixed amount of blocks

136
00:06:04,366 --> 00:06:06,366
now we can just keep looking around

137
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:09,033
until we find the ores we are looking for

138
00:06:09,033 --> 00:06:12,100
and we get a better yield by breaking those with a hammer

139
00:06:12,133 --> 00:06:13,966
and during our mining operation

140
00:06:13,966 --> 00:06:16,800
we found one more hazard we weren't ready for

141
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:19,833
some minerals are toxic and will poison us

142
00:06:19,833 --> 00:06:22,600
and it looks like the poison was strong enough that

143
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:25,300
even after getting rid of the hazardous material

144
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:26,866
we still pass out

145
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:29,600
this lead us to an even more annoying issue

146
00:06:29,666 --> 00:06:33,000
we respawned almost 4000 blocks away

147
00:06:33,066 --> 00:06:38,233
and having to walk all the way to our settlement every time this happens is not a good thing

148
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:41,266
so after walking all the way back to the mine

149
00:06:41,266 --> 00:06:42,366
making a backup

150
00:06:42,366 --> 00:06:44,066
isolating the toxic stuff

151
00:06:44,066 --> 00:06:45,700
and retrieving our stuff

152
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:47,466
we start working on a bed

153
00:06:47,466 --> 00:06:49,700
this will need some soft material

154
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:52,800
and the easiest way is to just roughly mold a sword

155
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:55,766
to collect some sheepskin from some alpackers

156
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:58,500
we can separate the wool from the leather with a knife

157
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:00,966
but it's still too rough to be used

158
00:07:00,966 --> 00:07:04,266
so we use a spindle to make it into yarns

159
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:05,833
then with the help of a loom

160
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:06,966
we make some cloth

161
00:07:06,966 --> 00:07:09,200
which we can finally use for our bed

162
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,900
now we will respawn at our base

163
00:07:11,966 --> 00:07:14,000
the next issue we should worry about is

164
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,266
stocking up some food for the winter

165
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:19,633
the main issue is that most food expires quickly

166
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:23,866
but we can work around that by for example cooking it

167
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:26,666
and now that we have meet our basic needs

168
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:30,500
we shall work on meeting the basic needs of our upcoming factory

169
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:34,100
thus we start gathering a lot of copper rich stones

170
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:37,166
and to melt it we will need a lot of wood

171
00:07:37,233 --> 00:07:43,766
and here chopping down a whole tree into logs, sticks and saplings takes probably more time than doing it IRL

172
00:07:43,766 --> 00:07:46,300
luckily for whatever reason

173
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,833
we can speed up the process by crouching

174
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:51,566
thus leaving aside the small branches

175
00:07:51,566 --> 00:07:55,666
however while the lumber we obtained is good enough for a pottery Kiln

176
00:07:55,666 --> 00:07:58,166
it's not optimal for proper metal working

177
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:01,600
so we make a charcoal pit to turn it into better stuff

178
00:08:01,633 --> 00:08:04,500
to do so, we simply bury some log piles

179
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:06,400
and then pitch those on fire

180
00:08:06,566 --> 00:08:08,100
we must be very careful

181
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:10,200
the wood must not be in contact with air

182
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:12,566
or it will only leave ash behind

183
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,500
and after a day or so

184
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,033
the process completed

185
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:17,633
turning the logs into charcoal

186
00:08:17,633 --> 00:08:19,400
which we can now dig out

187
00:08:19,433 --> 00:08:22,000
then we stick some in a hole surrounded by rocks

188
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,466
and pitch it on fire

189
00:08:23,466 --> 00:08:25,700
making a rudimentary forge

190
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:28,400
we fill it with more charcoal, some molds

191
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:31,700
and then we throw in the raw minerals we want to melt

192
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,433
after enough time

193
00:08:33,433 --> 00:08:35,266
the metal will flow out of the rocks

194
00:08:35,266 --> 00:08:37,100
and fall into the molds

195
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:39,666
from which we can then extract ingots

196
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,266
to work with those ingots

197
00:08:41,266 --> 00:08:44,266
we will need some hard material to smash those on

198
00:08:44,266 --> 00:08:47,033
but the rocks we have here are too soft

199
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:50,233
we found a rock hard enough for the task in our cave

200
00:08:50,233 --> 00:08:53,200
but bringing it back home is no easy task

201
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,866
if we use our pickaxe

202
00:08:54,866 --> 00:08:57,033
the rocks breaks into pebbles

203
00:08:57,166 --> 00:08:59,200
same things happens with a hammer

204
00:08:59,366 --> 00:09:02,166
the way we can actually extract a whole cube of rock

205
00:09:02,166 --> 00:09:05,300
is by breaking all of the connected blocks that touch it

206
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:07,566
leaving it almost floating into air

207
00:09:07,566 --> 00:09:10,366
at which point it falls as a single piece

208
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:13,666
we bring that piece of Hard Rock next to our forge

209
00:09:13,666 --> 00:09:15,800
and turn it into a primitive anvil

210
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,233
the first thing we will want to do with it

211
00:09:18,233 --> 00:09:20,800
is meld together two copper ingots

212
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,000
but of course

213
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,600
no matter how much we smash those together

214
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,466
we first have to heat them up

215
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:28,566
so we fire up our forge

216
00:09:28,566 --> 00:09:32,100
and wait for the ingots to become hot enough to glow orange

217
00:09:32,433 --> 00:09:34,966
then before they melt or cool down

218
00:09:34,966 --> 00:09:36,600
we take those to the anvil

219
00:09:36,833 --> 00:09:41,500
but moving glowing hot ingots with our bare hands wasn't our brightest idea

220
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:43,366
to help us with the task

221
00:09:43,366 --> 00:09:45,166
we get a couple of sticks

222
00:09:45,266 --> 00:09:46,700
but in the meantime

223
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:49,100
the ingots cooled down too much

224
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:51,200
so we heat up those again

225
00:09:51,433 --> 00:09:56,200
and we better have some molds to safeguard eventual molten metal spills

226
00:09:56,366 --> 00:09:58,133
once we reach temperature

227
00:09:58,133 --> 00:10:00,000
we try again to weld those

228
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,433
and this time

229
00:10:01,433 --> 00:10:04,800
we realize we also need some fluxing material

230
00:10:04,966 --> 00:10:05,700
luckily

231
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:08,500
the soft stone we have here is a sedimentary rock

232
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,666
which can be smashed into flux

233
00:10:10,666 --> 00:10:14,000
and with that we can finally get a double ingot

234
00:10:14,266 --> 00:10:16,266
don't mind the missing texture

235
00:10:16,433 --> 00:10:17,766
with enough of those

236
00:10:17,766 --> 00:10:19,800
we can make a slightly better anvil

237
00:10:20,033 --> 00:10:21,833
this one not only looks better

238
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:25,233
but it will also allow us to work harder materials

239
00:10:25,233 --> 00:10:26,700
such as bronze

240
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:27,933
long story short

241
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:29,966
we now have a bronze anvil

242
00:10:30,166 --> 00:10:32,766
but a proper anvil is made at least of iron

243
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,400
but at the moment

244
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:37,866
we do not have the tools to melt the iron out of rocks

245
00:10:37,866 --> 00:10:40,466
instead we have to work it in a bloomery

246
00:10:40,566 --> 00:10:43,633
and that machine requires quite a lot of bronze

247
00:10:43,633 --> 00:10:45,400
and that means a lot of copper

248
00:10:45,533 --> 00:10:46,700
to save on copper

249
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:48,866
we can use a different kind of bronze

250
00:10:48,866 --> 00:10:50,566
which can be made with less copper

251
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:54,600
and instead uses some less useful and more abundant minerals

252
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:56,166
bismuth bronze

253
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:59,266
and we can also increase the yield of our copper ores

254
00:10:59,266 --> 00:11:02,233
by first cleaning some of the impurities in a river

255
00:11:02,233 --> 00:11:04,366
and then smashing it into a finer powder

256
00:11:04,366 --> 00:11:06,633
to ease the extraction of molten metal

257
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:09,300
finally we wash off the soluble dust

258
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:11,500
and we are left with pure mineral dust

259
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:14,300
which will yield almost twice as much metal

260
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,500
allowing us to overflow a vessel

261
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:20,066
thus turning all of our precious minerals into trash

262
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:22,700
and now we have to gather more and start over

263
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:25,300
paying attention not to overflow the vessel

264
00:11:25,433 --> 00:11:26,533
for the next task

265
00:11:26,533 --> 00:11:28,966
having a double ingot won't be enough

266
00:11:29,066 --> 00:11:31,466
we have to hammer it into a proper plate

267
00:11:31,466 --> 00:11:33,366
and it must be done properly

268
00:11:33,433 --> 00:11:35,566
this means we have to keep hitting the thing 

269
00:11:35,566 --> 00:11:37,033
until it's flat enough

270
00:11:37,033 --> 00:11:38,633
but without any hole

271
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:40,100
after enough hammering

272
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:42,266
we managed to get our first plate

273
00:11:42,566 --> 00:11:44,166
but that was too thin

274
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,366
so we made a second one

275
00:11:46,366 --> 00:11:47,833
heated both of those up

276
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,833
and hammered them into a thicker one

277
00:11:50,466 --> 00:11:51,466
14 plates later

278
00:11:51,466 --> 00:11:53,433
we managed to make a bloomery

279
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,200
but to use that

280
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,466
we also need some bricks

281
00:11:57,566 --> 00:12:00,266
so we dissolve some lime in water

282
00:12:00,266 --> 00:12:01,100
add some sand

283
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:03,833
and let it in for a couple of hours to get mortar

284
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:07,466
next we take some of the pebbles we made while gathering ores

285
00:12:07,466 --> 00:12:09,400
and chisel those into bricks

286
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,566
which we then turn into blocks

287
00:12:11,666 --> 00:12:14,566
we used those to build a chimney for our broomery

288
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:17,766
and since those bricks are cheap and nice looking

289
00:12:17,766 --> 00:12:21,400
we also used them to made the walls of our future house

290
00:12:21,466 --> 00:12:26,000
next we throw some iron rich minerals with some charcoal in our broomery

291
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,600
and pitch it on fire

292
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:29,833
this process will take a long time

293
00:12:29,833 --> 00:12:32,466
and it will leave us with some iron blooms

294
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:34,766
we dig those out using a pickaxe

295
00:12:34,766 --> 00:12:36,833
then with the help of an anvil

296
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:39,666
we hammer those into wrought iron ingots

297
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,066
which we use to upgrade our anvil

298
00:12:42,366 --> 00:12:43,966
the next tier is steel

299
00:12:43,966 --> 00:12:47,033
but to get it we have a longer road ahead

300
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:49,200
we will need a couple of new machinery

301
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:53,000
but it all starts from a basic material we don't even have

302
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:53,766
pink clay

303
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,000
the main issue is that

304
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:59,433
this material can only be found in the humid and hot tropical biomes

305
00:12:59,433 --> 00:13:01,000
which are far from us

306
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:05,266
and it looks like we have to find a way around the ocean if we want to get there

307
00:13:05,266 --> 00:13:08,233
the best way to achieve so is probably to get a boat

308
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:10,100
and we have many choices

309
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:12,233
but not all of them are available

310
00:13:12,233 --> 00:13:15,433
some are expensive and require steel

311
00:13:15,433 --> 00:13:16,066
anyways

312
00:13:16,066 --> 00:13:19,500
the first step for making a good enough boat is some scaffolding

313
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,900
to hold it in place while we build it

314
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:23,600
next we need the planks

315
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:26,366
that will actually constitute the structure

316
00:13:26,433 --> 00:13:27,900
and to stick everything together

317
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:30,266
we can use some copper bolts

318
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:33,400
which we can make by first hammering an ingot into a rod

319
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:35,100
and then cutting it with a saw

320
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:37,066
and while working on the anvils

321
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:39,600
we also smite a couple of oar locks

322
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:41,466
finally we get a couple of ore

323
00:13:41,466 --> 00:13:44,000
so that we can start assembling the thing

324
00:13:44,033 --> 00:13:47,366
we start by building a structure with the scaffolds

325
00:13:47,366 --> 00:13:49,766
then we fill it up using the planks

326
00:13:49,766 --> 00:13:51,600
next with the help of a hammer

327
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:53,966
we insert the copper bolts into the structure

328
00:13:53,966 --> 00:13:55,666
to keep everything in place

329
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:57,833
and to complete our new boat

330
00:13:57,833 --> 00:13:59,366
we add the oar locks

331
00:13:59,433 --> 00:14:02,266
to use it we add the oars and jump on it

332
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:04,800
this ship is powered by the magical oars

333
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:06,700
that work whenever you stare at them

334
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:09,200
and before we take off to the sea

335
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,866
with our hunger for adventures

336
00:14:10,866 --> 00:14:14,233
we add some chests for extra inventory for our loot

337
00:14:14,366 --> 00:14:16,400
we should have probably took some food

338
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,366
some water and a backpack

339
00:14:18,366 --> 00:14:20,566
but I think a backup will suffice

340
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:23,666
and after a really long adventure across the ocean

341
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:25,400
we finally found land

342
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:28,666
but after the first phase of happiness

343
00:14:28,666 --> 00:14:30,666
the long chain of despair came

344
00:14:30,833 --> 00:14:32,466
this was just an island

345
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:35,400
next to it another volcanic island

346
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:37,033
and Big Sandy shore island

347
00:14:37,033 --> 00:14:38,700
with nothing interesting on them

348
00:14:39,033 --> 00:14:42,000
luckily not too far we found again land

349
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,366
this time a continent made of hills

350
00:14:44,366 --> 00:14:46,366
we found many new plants there

351
00:14:46,366 --> 00:14:48,966
but not luck with the clay we were looking for

352
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:52,100
so we started circum navigating it

353
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:54,066
but to avoid a swamp

354
00:14:54,066 --> 00:14:57,300
we moved inside the continent in a river to check it out

355
00:14:57,466 --> 00:15:00,800
and it was then that we spotted a suspicious red flower

356
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:02,866
upon closer inspection

357
00:15:02,866 --> 00:15:04,766
it actually was the blood Lily

358
00:15:04,766 --> 00:15:07,633
which only spawns above the clay we are looking for

359
00:15:07,966 --> 00:15:11,400
however after digging we didn't find anything

360
00:15:11,866 --> 00:15:13,766
and the flower now lost it petals

361
00:15:13,766 --> 00:15:16,000
and looks like normal grass

362
00:15:16,233 --> 00:15:18,566
but after a few more steps

363
00:15:18,566 --> 00:15:20,566
we finally found the pink clay

364
00:15:20,566 --> 00:15:25,666
just below another flower which decided to unbloom to make the search harder for us

365
00:15:25,866 --> 00:15:29,566
we fill our inventory and our ship with all of that pink gold

366
00:15:29,566 --> 00:15:31,200
then we head back home

367
00:15:31,433 --> 00:15:32,900
and when we park our ship

368
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:36,000
we notice the wind was pushing it to the open sea

369
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:39,366
since we do not have the steel for a pole to keep it leashed

370
00:15:39,366 --> 00:15:41,366
we enclose it in our new pool

371
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:43,000
now that we have the clay

372
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,866
we have to dry it into powder

373
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,133
to heat it up

374
00:15:46,133 --> 00:15:47,900
we fire up our forge

375
00:15:48,033 --> 00:15:50,033
however after not much

376
00:15:50,033 --> 00:15:53,500
we realize this process is rather slow and tedious

377
00:15:53,666 --> 00:15:55,433
to make it easier to manage

378
00:15:55,433 --> 00:15:58,033
instead of heating single pieces of clay

379
00:15:58,033 --> 00:16:00,433
we fill up a vessel and heat that instead

380
00:16:00,566 --> 00:16:04,100
after a long time and a lot of charcoal it worked

381
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:07,000
but our vessel is now too hot to be opened

382
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:09,433
so we cool it down in a water bath

383
00:16:09,566 --> 00:16:12,466
with that we now have our kaolinite clay powder

384
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:14,666
but that wasn't really enough

385
00:16:14,666 --> 00:16:16,166
so repeat the process

386
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:20,066
and this time we use a Kiln pit instead of the forge

387
00:16:20,066 --> 00:16:21,100
while we wait

388
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:25,133
we can work on the other ingredient required for the next step

389
00:16:25,133 --> 00:16:25,666
graphite

390
00:16:25,966 --> 00:16:27,066
and to locate it

391
00:16:27,066 --> 00:16:29,033
we can follow our best buddy

392
00:16:29,033 --> 00:16:29,966
Diamond buds

393
00:16:29,966 --> 00:16:33,200
those indicate and underneath carbon vein

394
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:37,666
and we can already gather some tiny amounts of graphite on the surface

395
00:16:37,933 --> 00:16:39,066
after some digging

396
00:16:39,066 --> 00:16:39,966
we found a cave

397
00:16:39,966 --> 00:16:43,166
which also exposed the mineral we were looking for

398
00:16:43,166 --> 00:16:44,266
we collect some of it

399
00:16:44,266 --> 00:16:46,700
and then we process it into pure dust

400
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:48,633
but it wasn't dusty enough

401
00:16:48,633 --> 00:16:52,433
so we use our new quern to grind it down into a finer powder

402
00:16:52,433 --> 00:16:54,633
we mix it with the other two kinds of clay

403
00:16:54,633 --> 00:16:55,766
into fire clay

404
00:16:55,766 --> 00:16:58,033
which we can mold into a crucible

405
00:16:58,133 --> 00:17:00,233
and as with normal clay

406
00:17:00,233 --> 00:17:02,100
we have to fire it up in the forge

407
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,966
to turn it into ceramic

408
00:17:03,966 --> 00:17:05,566
but after a long wait

409
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:08,033
we figured out this wasn't going to work

410
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:10,233
we have to heat it up at yellow white 4

411
00:17:10,633 --> 00:17:14,366
however our charcoal burns at yellow white 2

412
00:17:14,466 --> 00:17:17,033
one solution could be using a better fuel

413
00:17:17,033 --> 00:17:20,500
such as the coal we found in the diamond graphite vein

414
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:22,433
but we don't have much of it

415
00:17:22,433 --> 00:17:24,800
so we keep it for better purposes

416
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:26,966
instead we work on the new tool

417
00:17:26,966 --> 00:17:30,800
which start from taking the hide left over from processing wool

418
00:17:30,866 --> 00:17:33,200
this one is too rough and dirty

419
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,900
so we start the cleaning process

420
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,966
by sinking it into lime water

421
00:17:37,033 --> 00:17:39,266
then to get a sturdy table

422
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:41,700
we get a lumber and clean it from it bark

423
00:17:41,866 --> 00:17:44,066
now we can lay the prepared hide on it

424
00:17:44,066 --> 00:17:46,366
and start the scratching process

425
00:17:46,366 --> 00:17:48,700
once we finish scratching the hide

426
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:50,633
we put it in a barrel with fresh water

427
00:17:50,633 --> 00:17:52,666
to clean up all the residues

428
00:17:52,666 --> 00:17:55,700
finally after preparing some tanning agent

429
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,466
we soak the cleaned hide in it to get proper leather

430
00:17:58,466 --> 00:18:01,100
with this we can now craft our new tool

431
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:03,433
to boost the temperature of our forge

432
00:18:03,433 --> 00:18:04,300
bellow

433
00:18:04,366 --> 00:18:07,266
and it was then that we realized it's already winter

434
00:18:07,266 --> 00:18:09,266
and we still don't have a roof

435
00:18:09,266 --> 00:18:13,366
so after quickly using our new toy to complete the crucible

436
00:18:13,366 --> 00:18:15,366
we also complete our roof

437
00:18:15,366 --> 00:18:19,233
and this place not only is cold enough for icicles to form

438
00:18:19,233 --> 00:18:21,000
it is also quite dark

439
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:24,000
and torches here burn out after two days

440
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,600
we can nap a pumpkin to obtain a decoration

441
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,200
that will double the duration

442
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,900
but it's still not much

443
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:32,200
another cool option is to make lamps

444
00:18:32,633 --> 00:18:36,033
but those are cool to make only the first time

445
00:18:36,066 --> 00:18:38,766
the first step is to get the metal frame

446
00:18:38,766 --> 00:18:40,366
which we can do in the anvil

447
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:42,300
and then we need the glass

448
00:18:42,300 --> 00:18:44,000
we prepare the base compound

449
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,866
by mixing a couple of easy to gather materials

450
00:18:46,866 --> 00:18:50,300
then we apply that over a ceramic blowpipe and heat it up

451
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:52,200
once we get it in our hands

452
00:18:52,266 --> 00:18:55,433
it's too hot so we instinctively throw it away

453
00:18:55,433 --> 00:18:57,233
after getting a second blowpipe

454
00:18:57,233 --> 00:18:59,300
to prevent burns from the first one

455
00:18:59,300 --> 00:19:04,966
we start trying to figure out how to manage all the tools we have to use to do our glasswork

456
00:19:04,966 --> 00:19:05,900
as usual

457
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:09,433
we can find a better explanation in the TerraFirm guide book

458
00:19:09,433 --> 00:19:13,100
so with the help of a blowpipe in one hand

459
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:15,833
we take the hot blowpipe with the other hand

460
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:16,766
we swap tools

461
00:19:16,766 --> 00:19:19,433
and then we blow in the pipe with the hot glass

462
00:19:19,666 --> 00:19:21,000
then we pinch it

463
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:25,366
and before it gets too cold to the point it can no longer be worked

464
00:19:25,366 --> 00:19:27,566
we put it back in the forge

465
00:19:27,833 --> 00:19:29,266
once we get it back

466
00:19:29,266 --> 00:19:31,766
we hit it with a paddle and then blow again

467
00:19:31,966 --> 00:19:38,233
finally we heat it up one last time before we cut out the molded glass sphere for our lantern

468
00:19:38,466 --> 00:19:41,500
we can combine it with the metal frame to get a lantern

469
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:44,600
but of course that still needs fuel

470
00:19:44,766 --> 00:19:47,466
for that we can use creosote oil

471
00:19:47,466 --> 00:19:50,666
which we can feed with pipes from our new coke oven

472
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:54,933
the only thing left to do is to light it up using an already lit torch

473
00:19:54,966 --> 00:19:57,633
with that touch of light and technology

474
00:19:57,633 --> 00:19:59,366
our shelter looks a new

475
00:19:59,633 --> 00:20:01,833
but while this is nice and all

476
00:20:01,833 --> 00:20:04,300
there are other issues we have to face

477
00:20:04,433 --> 00:20:06,700
the lake nearby our house is icing

478
00:20:06,766 --> 00:20:09,166
thus making water more of an issue

479
00:20:09,266 --> 00:20:10,500
to help with that

480
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:11,900
we craft an iron flask

481
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:14,766
that will help us bring water wherever we go

482
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:18,000
and we fill it with the water leftover from working leather

483
00:20:18,166 --> 00:20:21,633
now we can sip fresh clean water wherever we want

484
00:20:21,766 --> 00:20:23,266
but other than water

485
00:20:23,266 --> 00:20:25,466
we also need some better food

486
00:20:25,633 --> 00:20:30,366
we can get some by grinding into finer powder some of our wheat leftovers

487
00:20:30,466 --> 00:20:34,166
then we take some water and make a dough with that flour

488
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,800
we make some bread loaves

489
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:39,400
and cook those with the help of grill to better control the cooking

490
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:42,000
finally we add some veggies and meat

491
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,266
to make some nice sandwiches

492
00:20:44,366 --> 00:20:47,933
but one other food we can make more ideal for this climate is soup

493
00:20:47,933 --> 00:20:50,966
we put a pot on the fire and fill it with water

494
00:20:50,966 --> 00:20:54,233
then we add some ingredients and make it boil

495
00:20:54,233 --> 00:20:55,266
once it's done

496
00:20:55,266 --> 00:20:56,666
we fill some bowls

497
00:20:56,666 --> 00:20:58,300
and have a nice feast

498
00:20:58,366 --> 00:20:59,700
the only thing we need now 

499
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:02,800
is a better way to carry all of those new things

500
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:04,400
and to carry all of that weight

501
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:07,066
we shall use something made of a strong material

502
00:21:07,066 --> 00:21:08,633
such as jute fibre

503
00:21:08,866 --> 00:21:11,233
which we loom into burlap cloth

504
00:21:11,233 --> 00:21:13,833
with that we can assemble a backpack

505
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:17,766
finally we can bring our anvils with us wherever we go

506
00:21:17,766 --> 00:21:19,600
without getting slowed down

507
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,700
and this is going to be our new best friend

508
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:25,400
when we will be gathering more iron for the upcoming episode

509
00:21:25,566 --> 00:21:27,100
see you next time

510
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:28,233
bye bye

511
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:01,266
大家好

512
00:00:01,266 --> 00:00:04,666
今天我们要开始TerrafirmaGreg旅程了

513
00:00:04,666 --> 00:00:06,666
正如这个整合包名

514
00:00:06,666 --> 00:00:10,166
这是一个围绕群峦传说和给格雷科技的整合包

515
00:00:10,200 --> 00:00:12,600
但同时也有很多机械动力内容

516
00:00:12,700 --> 00:00:14,266
作为一个群峦包

517
00:00:14,266 --> 00:00:17,066
世界生成被大改了

518
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:19,966

而且还有更多事要担心


519
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,800
首先是食物

520
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:24,133
尽管食物遍地都是

521
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:26,300
但它们都有保质期

522
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:29,366
而且我们不能只吃一种食物

523
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:31,500
我们必须保证营养均衡

524
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,500
来避免引发问题

525
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:36,933
而且为了避免因为脱水而晕过去

526
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:39,400
我们必须记得补充液体

527
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:39,800
最后

528
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:44,300

我们也要关注温度和季节


529
00:00:44,300 --> 00:00:47,333
既然我们出生在了一个很冷的地方

530
00:00:47,366 --> 00:00:51,400
我们应该启程去到一个更温暖的地带

531
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,633
所以我们开始向南进发

532
00:00:53,666 --> 00:00:55,466
与此同时

533
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:57,866
我们应该开始准备过夜

534
00:00:57,866 --> 00:00:59,866
tfc的夜晚不会有什么危险生物

535
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:01,400
但仍然会很黑

536
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:03,566
所以我们捡几根树枝

537
00:01:03,566 --> 00:01:06,266
做了一把钻木取火的工具

538
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,300
随后我们确保这东西可用

539
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:11,400
但这样随手点的火没什么用

540
00:01:11,400 --> 00:01:14,633
所以我们开始做一些有用的工具

541
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:18,400
我们把先前收集的石头打制成斧头

542
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:20,333
并把它绑在一个斧柄上

543
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:21,933
现在我们有了把斧头

544
00:01:21,966 --> 00:01:25,066
可以砍树来收集点木材

545
00:01:25,066 --> 00:01:28,966
但砍这些大树很耗时

546
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,800
所以我们转而寻找一些已经倒下的树

547
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:35,033
这些干枯朽木腐朽到了

548
00:01:35,066 --> 00:01:38,066
会自己倒下

549
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,033
有了这些木材

550
00:01:39,066 --> 00:01:42,200
我们可以做一个可控的篝火

551
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,400
除此之外还需要加两个树枝

552
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:46,300
来辅助点火

553
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:47,600
尽管如此

554
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:51,066
我们仍然要花时间尝试几次才能点起火

555
00:01:51,100 --> 00:01:53,400
现在我们有了篝火

556
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:56,566
可以用来缓慢地点燃一些木棍

557
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:58,000
来做火把

558
00:01:58,066 --> 00:01:59,066
有了这些

559
00:01:59,066 --> 00:02:03,466
我们现在可以昼夜兼行了

560
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:20,500
几天几夜的徒步后

561
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:24,866
我们发现自己被困在了被海洋环绕的一个大岛上

562
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,166
尽管我们找到了还不错的气候区

563
00:02:28,166 --> 00:02:31,366
但那地方并不适合定居

564
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:34,200
所以我们决定往回走一点

565
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:35,966
到一个气候不算恶劣

566
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:37,666
但植被很丰富的地区

567
00:02:37,666 --> 00:02:40,866
现在我们找到了一片建家的好地方

568
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:44,600
也得给我们背包里的这堆破烂找个家

569
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:45,400
为此

570
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:49,133
我们在河边收集一些黏土

571
00:02:49,200 --> 00:02:50,300
在这个整合包里

572
00:02:50,300 --> 00:02:52,766
黏土不仅会像沙子一样有重力

573
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:56,400
在你挖掉它旁边的方块时它还会向侧边滑落

574
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:59,400
总之为了加快收集黏土的速度

575
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:01,233
我们又打了一些石头

576
00:03:01,266 --> 00:03:03,066
来做铲子

577
00:03:03,066 --> 00:03:04,466
一旦我们收集了足够多

578
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:08,400
我们就花一整晚来将它们捏成各种形状

579
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:10,600
你可能看出来了

580
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:14,600
要存下这些物品，我们最需要的是大缸

581
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:17,600
但是刚捏出来的黏土缸还太软

582
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:19,566
为了将它烧成能用的陶罐

583
00:03:19,566 --> 00:03:21,600
我们把它放进坑里

584
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:23,733
覆盖上干草和木材

585
00:03:23,766 --> 00:03:24,766
并将其点燃

586
00:03:24,766 --> 00:03:26,966
烧制需要8分钟

587
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:30,800
而且我们最好保证旁边没有可燃物

588
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:33,400
下雨不会影响烧陶器的进度

589
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:36,300
但雨也许能帮我们灭一灭火

590
00:03:36,300 --> 00:03:36,733
也许吧

591
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:39,400
等待它完成的时候

592
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:42,166
我们可以为下个任务做更多准备

593
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,200
也就是冶金

594
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:48,400

因此我们为青铜工具制作了铸模


595
00:03:48,566 --> 00:03:49,766
再一次地

596
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:53,000
我们挖了坑，并用燃料把铸模埋进坑里

597
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:55,200
随后点火

598
00:03:55,200 --> 00:03:57,766
我们又制作了更多模具

599
00:03:57,800 --> 00:04:00,000
等待烧制的时间里

600
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:02,033
我们可以在家周围逛逛

601
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:03,666
找一些地表的矿粒

602
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:06,800
现在我们主要找锡和铜

603
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,333
收集了一些矿粒之后

604
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,600
我们回家

605
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:11,566
我们的第一个大缸已经准备好了

606
00:04:11,566 --> 00:04:14,766
终于可以用它来释放一些背包空间

607
00:04:14,866 --> 00:04:16,800
大缸还有一个很好的特性

608
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,033
关上缸盖后

609
00:04:18,066 --> 00:04:20,766
其中的食物保质期会延长一倍

610
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,066
接着我们拿出小缸

611
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:26,900
它们可以当成小背包用

612
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:29,100
但它的主要功能是熔化金属

613
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:32,700
我们可以熔化一些黝铜矿来获得铜

614
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,366
但我们想要的是青铜

615
00:04:34,366 --> 00:04:34,900
要获得青铜

616
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:37,466
我们需要在冶炼时加入一些锡石

617
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:39,366
合金的比例不是特别严格

618
00:04:39,366 --> 00:04:42,866
将它保持在那个区间里就可以

619
00:04:43,066 --> 00:04:45,633
我们只需要将指针悬停在物品上

620
00:04:45,633 --> 00:04:49,000
看tooltip里的生成物提示就好了

621
00:04:49,100 --> 00:04:50,200

一但我们觉得满意


622
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,800
我们就点燃坑窑来熔炼它们

623
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:55,600
等火一灭

624
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:59,400
我们在它还热得让金属保持液态的时候就立刻拿起小缸

625
00:04:59,400 --> 00:05:02,400
我们用它做的第一个东西是锯片

626
00:05:02,400 --> 00:05:04,966
我们又设法做了探矿镐

627
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,600
和一把普通镐子

628
00:05:06,666 --> 00:05:08,800
一旦金属冷却

629
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,333
我们就将其脱模

630
00:05:10,366 --> 00:05:13,000

并用来合成一些可使用的工具


631
00:05:13,100 --> 00:05:17,100
我们用新锯子从原木中切出木材

632
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:20,400
好用来做工作台和箱子

633
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:22,400
做完我们才发现

634
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:25,066
我们选的木头太难看了

635
00:05:25,066 --> 00:05:28,066
所以我们将它们全部换成了更好看的材质

636
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:29,833
但接下来的冒险中

637
00:05:29,866 --> 00:05:31,266
我们还需要更多金属

638
00:05:31,266 --> 00:05:34,000
而地表的金属粒完全不够用‘

639
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,833
为了找到更大的矿脉

640
00:05:35,866 --> 00:05:38,833
我们在金属粒周围使用勘矿镐

641
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:41,166
来确定地表的矿物分布

642
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:42,900
一旦我们定位到一些矿石

643
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:45,133
我们就向下挖掘

644
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,000
但这里是群峦

645
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:50,600
就算挖洞也比想象中难

646
00:05:50,766 --> 00:05:52,266
如果我们不够小心

647
00:05:52,300 --> 00:05:54,500
就连硬质岩石也会砸在我们身上

648
00:05:54,666 --> 00:05:55,866
为了防止坍塌

649
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,600
我们需要支撑梁

650
00:05:57,600 --> 00:06:00,833
每一根支撑梁都会防止周围的方块坠落

651
00:06:00,866 --> 00:06:04,366
我们每隔一段距离就放一些

652
00:06:04,366 --> 00:06:06,366
现在我们可以在矿道里寻找

653
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:09,000
直到找到我们需要的矿物

654
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:12,066
用锤子采矿可以增产

655
00:06:12,100 --> 00:06:13,933
在采矿的过程中

656
00:06:13,966 --> 00:06:16,766
我们遇到了未预料的危险

657
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:19,800
一些矿物是有毒的，会毒害我们

658
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:22,566
且似乎这种毒性强到

659
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:25,300
即便我们丢掉这些有毒矿物

660
00:06:25,300 --> 00:06:26,866
我们仍然被毒死了

661
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:29,600
这给我们带来了一个更烦人的问题

662
00:06:29,666 --> 00:06:32,966

我们重生在了4000格外的位置


663
00:06:33,066 --> 00:06:38,200
每次我们死亡后都要跑这么远不是一件好事

664
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:41,233
所以在长途跋涉回到矿道后

665
00:06:41,266 --> 00:06:42,366
我们存了一个备份

666
00:06:42,366 --> 00:06:44,066
挑出有毒矿物

667
00:06:44,066 --> 00:06:45,666
并捡回了我们的尸体

668
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:47,466
我们开始准备做床

669
00:06:47,466 --> 00:06:49,666
这需要一些柔软的材料

670
00:06:49,700 --> 00:06:52,800
最简单的方法就是随便做一把剑

671
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:55,766
然后去找羊驼们借一点羊皮

672
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:58,500
用小刀把羊毛从羊皮上弄下来

673
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:00,966
但这样的羊毛还是粗制的不能直接用

674
00:07:00,966 --> 00:07:04,266
所以我们用纺锤将其纺成羊毛纱

675
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:05,800
随后在织布机的帮助下

676
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:06,933
我们获得了一些羊毛布

677
00:07:06,966 --> 00:07:09,166
可以用来做床

678
00:07:09,200 --> 00:07:11,900
现在我们就可以重生在家里了

679
00:07:11,966 --> 00:07:13,966
我们要关心的第二件事是

680
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:16,266
为过冬而准备的食物

681
00:07:16,300 --> 00:07:19,600
问题在于大多数食物过期得很快

682
00:07:19,700 --> 00:07:23,866
但我们有办法解决，比如将它烤熟

683
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:26,666
而现在我们已经满足了生存的基本需求

684
00:07:26,666 --> 00:07:30,466
是时候着手于即将到来的工业化了

685
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:34,100
于是我们开始收集大量的铜矿石

686
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:37,166
将其熔炼，我们还需要很多木头

687
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:40,066
然而在这里砍树花的时间

688
00:07:40,066 --> 00:07:43,733
大概比现实里砍倒一棵树还要久

689
00:07:43,766 --> 00:07:46,266
不过幸运的是，不知出于什么原因

690
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,800
蹲下的同时砍树会获得加速

691
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:51,533
同时还不会产生副产的木棍

692
00:07:51,566 --> 00:07:55,666
我们费劲获得的木材烧陶器还不错

693
00:07:55,666 --> 00:07:58,166
但并不适合金属加工

694
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:01,600
所以我们做了一个木炭坑来制炭

695
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:04,466
只需要在坑里埋一些原木

696
00:08:04,500 --> 00:08:06,400
然后点火

697
00:08:06,566 --> 00:08:08,066
我们必须小心

698
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:10,200
不能让燃烧的木头和空气接触

699
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:12,566
否则它们会烧成灰烬

700
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,500
过一天左右

701
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:16,000
烧制完成了

702
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,600
木头被烧成了木炭

703
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:19,366
我们现在可以把它们挖下来

704
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:21,966
随后我们把木炭摆进由石头环绕的坑里

705
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,466
点上火

706
00:08:23,466 --> 00:08:25,666
获得了一个基础的木炭炉

707
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:28,366
我们添加一些木炭和铸模

708
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:31,700
再放入我们想熔炼的矿石

709
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,400
足够长时间后

710
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:35,233
熔融金属会流出矿石

711
00:08:35,266 --> 00:08:37,066
再流进铸模里

712
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:39,666
之后我们就可以从中取出金属锭

713
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,266
要加工这些金属锭

714
00:08:41,266 --> 00:08:44,266
我们需要一些足够硬的材料来将锭放在上面锤锻

715
00:08:44,266 --> 00:08:47,000
但这里的石头都太软了

716
00:08:47,300 --> 00:08:50,200
我们在矿洞里找到了足够硬的石头

717
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:53,166
但把它们带回家不是件容易的事情

718
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,866
如果我们用镐子挖掉

719
00:08:54,866 --> 00:08:57,000
它会碎成石子

720
00:08:57,166 --> 00:08:59,166
就算用锤子也一样

721
00:08:59,366 --> 00:09:02,166
要完整取得一块石头

722
00:09:02,166 --> 00:09:05,266
我们需要破坏与目标相连的所有方块

723
00:09:05,300 --> 00:09:07,566
使之几乎悬空

724
00:09:07,566 --> 00:09:10,366
随后它会以一整个方块掉落

725
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:13,666
我们把这块坚硬的石头带回到木炭炉旁边

726
00:09:13,666 --> 00:09:15,766
用锤子将其变成石砧

727
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,200
我们要用它做的第一件事

728
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:20,766
是焊接一个铜双锭

729
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,000
不过当然

730
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,600
不管我们如何敲打

731
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,466
都得先把它们加热

732
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:28,566
所以我们点起木炭炉

733
00:09:28,566 --> 00:09:32,066
等铜锭烧到橙温度

734
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:34,933
在它熔化或冷却之前

735
00:09:34,966 --> 00:09:36,566
我们将其放在砧上

736
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:41,466
但空手转移红热的金属锭不是个好主意

737
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:43,366
为了完成任务

738
00:09:43,366 --> 00:09:45,166
我们用一对木棍夹取它们

739
00:09:45,266 --> 00:09:46,666
但与此同时

740
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:49,100
它们已经冷却了

741
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:51,200
所以我们重新加热它们

742
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:54,100
我们最好放几个铸模做保险

743
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:56,166
以防金属熔化消失掉

744
00:09:56,366 --> 00:09:58,100
一旦到达可焊接温度

745
00:09:58,100 --> 00:09:59,966
我们再试一次焊接

746
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:01,400
而这一次

747
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:04,766
我们意识到还需要一些助焊剂

748
00:10:04,966 --> 00:10:05,666
幸运的是

749
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:08,500
我们周围的石头是沉积岩

750
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,666
它们可以被打碎成助焊剂

751
00:10:10,666 --> 00:10:13,966
有了这些，我们终于获得了双锭

752
00:10:14,266 --> 00:10:16,266
不要在意这个贴图丢失

753
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:17,733
有足够多的双锭后

754
00:10:17,766 --> 00:10:19,766
我们可以做出更好一点的砧

755
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,800
铜砧不只更好看

756
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:25,200
我们还可以用它处理更硬的金属

757
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,666
比如青铜

758
00:10:26,700 --> 00:10:27,900
总之

759
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:29,933
我们现在有了青铜砧

760
00:10:30,166 --> 00:10:32,766
但一个合格的砧起码得是铁做的

761
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,400
但暂时

762
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:37,866
我们没有能够从矿石中熔炼铁的工具

763
00:10:37,866 --> 00:10:40,466
相反，我们需要用锻铁炉进行加工

764
00:10:40,566 --> 00:10:43,600
而锻铁炉又需要相当多的青铜

765
00:10:43,600 --> 00:10:45,366
也意味着相当多的铜

766
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:46,666
为了节约铜

767
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:48,866
我们可以换一种青铜

768
00:10:48,866 --> 00:10:50,566
它需求更少的铜

769
00:10:50,566 --> 00:10:54,566
取而代之的是一些不那么有用但储量更丰富的矿物

770
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,133
也就是铋青铜

771
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:59,266
我们还可以对铜矿进行增产

772
00:10:59,266 --> 00:11:02,200
首先用水洗去杂质

773
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:04,333
然后把它敲成更细的粉末

774
00:11:04,366 --> 00:11:06,600
使得熔炼更加容易

775
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:09,266
随后我们洗掉其中的可溶部分

776
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:11,500
只剩下纯净的矿粉

777
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:14,300
相比之下可以几乎增产一倍

778
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,500
这也使得产物溢出了小缸

779
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:20,066
让我们的珍贵矿石变成了垃圾

780
00:11:20,100 --> 00:11:22,700
现在我们只能再多收集一些

781
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:25,300
且注意不要让产量溢出容器

782
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,500
为了下一个任务

783
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,933
仅有双锭还不够

784
00:11:29,066 --> 00:11:31,466
我们必须将其锤锻成合格的板材

785
00:11:31,466 --> 00:11:33,366
而锤锻的过程必须适当

786
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:35,533
这意味着我们必须不停敲击

787
00:11:35,566 --> 00:11:37,000
使其足够平整

788
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,600
且没有孔洞

789
00:11:38,700 --> 00:11:40,100
经历了足够的锤锻后

790
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:42,266
我们获得了第一块板

791
00:11:42,566 --> 00:11:44,166
但它太单薄了

792
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,366
所以我们锻造了第二块

793
00:11:46,366 --> 00:11:47,800
将二者加热

794
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:49,800
并焊接在一起

795
00:11:50,466 --> 00:11:51,466
再做出14块板后

796
00:11:51,466 --> 00:11:53,400
我们最终做出了锻铁炉

797
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,200
但是，要使用它

798
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,466
我们还需要一些砖块

799
00:11:57,566 --> 00:12:00,266
我们将一些石灰溶入水中

800
00:12:00,266 --> 00:12:01,066
加入一些沙子

801
00:12:01,100 --> 00:12:03,800
并封存几个小时来获得砂浆

802
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:07,466
接下来我们拿一些挖矿时收集的石子

803
00:12:07,466 --> 00:12:09,366
用凿子将其凿成砖块

804
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:11,566
最后制成石砖方块

805
00:12:11,666 --> 00:12:14,566
我们用这些石砖建造了锻铁炉的烟囱

806
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:17,766
且这些砖块便宜又好看

807
00:12:17,766 --> 00:12:21,366
我们也将用它们来做我们未来的家的墙壁

808
00:12:21,466 --> 00:12:25,966
我们往锻铁炉里丟一些铁矿石和木炭

809
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:27,600
并点着火

810
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,800
冶炼需要花费很长时间

811
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:32,433
它会留下生铁方坯

812
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:34,766
我们用镐将它们挖出来

813
00:12:34,766 --> 00:12:36,800
接下来借助青铜砧

814
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:39,666
我们将它们锤锻成锻铁锭

815
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,066
随后用这些锻铁升级了砧

816
00:12:42,366 --> 00:12:43,966
下一阶段是钢

817
00:12:43,966 --> 00:12:47,000
但要获得它，我们还有很长的路要走

818
00:12:47,100 --> 00:12:49,166
我们需要一些新设备

819
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:53,000
但这些都要从一种我们尚未获得的材料开始

820
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:53,766
高岭土

821
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:55,000
最大的问题是

822
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:59,400
高岭土只能在潮湿又炎热的群系中找到

823
00:12:59,400 --> 00:13:00,966
离我们很远

824
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:05,266
要到达那的话，我们必须想办法跨越这片海洋

825
00:13:05,266 --> 00:13:08,200
最好的办法是做一艘船

826
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:10,066
并且在船的种类上我们还有不少选择

827
00:13:10,166 --> 00:13:12,200
但目前并不所有的都可选

828
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:15,400
有些船造价很贵且需要钢

829
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,033
总之

830
00:13:16,066 --> 00:13:19,466

做一艘足够好的船的第一步是做一些船架


831
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:21,900
好让我们在搭建时固定船体

832
00:13:22,100 --> 00:13:23,600
接下来是一些木板

833
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:26,366
用来构成船体结构

834
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,866
为了钉住所有方块

835
00:13:27,900 --> 00:13:30,266
我们可以做一些铜螺栓

836
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:33,400
我们先将锭锤锻成杆

837
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:35,100
随后用锯子将其切断

838
00:13:35,100 --> 00:13:37,066
与此同时

839
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:39,566
我们还做了一对桨座

840
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:41,466
最后再做一对船桨

841
00:13:41,466 --> 00:13:43,966
我们就可以开始组装船了

842
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:47,333
第一步用脚手架搭出结构

843
00:13:47,366 --> 00:13:49,766
再用木板填充

844
00:13:49,766 --> 00:13:51,566
接下来借助锤子的力量

845
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:53,966
我们将铜螺栓钉进船体结构

846
00:13:53,966 --> 00:13:55,666
好保证船不散架

847
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:57,800
为了完成我们的新船

848
00:13:57,800 --> 00:13:59,333
我们为之加上桨座

849
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:02,233
装上船桨，跳上去来使用这艘船

850
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:04,800
这艘船的动力源是魔法船桨

851
00:14:04,800 --> 00:14:06,700
只要你盯着它们看，它们就会转起来

852
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:09,200
在我们怀着探险的渴望

853
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:10,866
出海之前

854
00:14:10,866 --> 00:14:14,200
我们加装了一些箱子来作为储存战利品的额外空间

855
00:14:14,366 --> 00:14:16,366
我们还应该够带些食物

856
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:18,366
以及水和背包

857
00:14:18,366 --> 00:14:20,566
不过我觉得保存一个备份就足够了

858
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:23,666
在跨海的长途跋涉后

859
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:25,366
我们终于发现了新大陆

860
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:28,633
但最初的喜悦过后

861
00:14:28,666 --> 00:14:30,666
接踵而至的是更多的失望

862
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,433
我们发现的只是座岛

863
00:14:32,800 --> 00:14:35,366
紧挨着的是一个火山岛

864
00:14:35,400 --> 00:14:37,000
和另一个只有沙滩的大岛

865
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:38,666
同样什么都没有

866
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:39,733
但幸运的是

867
00:14:39,733 --> 00:14:41,966
在不远的地方我们再次发现了陆地

868
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,366
这次是一块由丘陵构成的大陆

869
00:14:44,366 --> 00:14:46,366
在这里我们找到了许多新植被

870
00:14:46,366 --> 00:14:48,966
但不幸的是并没有高岭土

871
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:52,100
所以我们开始绕海岸线航行

872
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:54,066
然而为了避开一片沼泽

873
00:14:54,066 --> 00:14:57,266
我们驶入一条从内陆流出来的河流来一探究竟

874
00:14:57,466 --> 00:15:00,766
就在那时我们发现了一种可疑的红色花

875
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,833
仔细观察后

876
00:15:02,866 --> 00:15:04,766
我们发现这是火球花

877
00:15:04,766 --> 00:15:07,600
而这种花只会长在高岭土之上

878
00:15:07,966 --> 00:15:11,366
然而挖掘后我们却什么都没找到

879
00:15:11,866 --> 00:15:13,766
而且那花此时也失去了花瓣

880
00:15:13,766 --> 00:15:15,966
看起来和普通的草没什么两样

881
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:18,533
但就在周围

882
00:15:18,566 --> 00:15:20,566
我们终于找到了高岭土

883
00:15:20,566 --> 00:15:25,666
就在那个决定谢掉花瓣来增添我们寻找难度的那朵花旁边

884
00:15:25,866 --> 00:15:29,566
我们用这些高岭土填满了背包

885
00:15:29,566 --> 00:15:31,166
随后回家

886
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:32,866
停好船后

887
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:36,000
我们意识到风在把我们的船推向大海

888
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:39,366
而我们还没有钢来制作柱子拴住船

889
00:15:39,366 --> 00:15:41,366
只好把它围在小水泊里

890
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:43,000
既然有了高岭土

891
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:44,866
我们就把它们烘干烤成粉末

892
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:46,100
为了加热它们

893
00:15:46,100 --> 00:15:47,866
我们点燃了木炭炉

894
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:50,000
然而没过多久

895
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:53,466
我们就意识到这样处理又慢又无聊

896
00:15:53,666 --> 00:15:55,400
为了简化流程

897
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:58,000
我们不再一个一个烧

898
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,400
取而代之的是用小缸装满后一起加热

899
00:16:00,566 --> 00:16:04,066
经过很长时间，耗费了很多木炭后，它终于完成了

900
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:06,966
但此时还太热，不能打开

901
00:16:07,066 --> 00:16:09,400
所以我们在水坑里冷却它

902
00:16:09,566 --> 00:16:12,466
现在我们有了高岭石粉

903
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:14,666
但这些实际上还不够

904
00:16:14,666 --> 00:16:16,166
所以我们重复这个过程

905
00:16:16,266 --> 00:16:20,066
这次我们换用坑窑代替木炭炉

906
00:16:20,066 --> 00:16:21,066
等待的时候

907
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:25,100
我们可以着手于下一个任务所需的材料

908
00:16:25,100 --> 00:16:25,633
石墨

909
00:16:25,966 --> 00:16:27,066
要找到它

910
00:16:27,066 --> 00:16:29,000
我们可以先找到我们最好的朋友

911
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:29,933
钻石芽

912
00:16:29,966 --> 00:16:33,166
它们指示着底下的含碳矿脉

913
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:37,666
并且我们已经可以在地表收集少量的石墨粉了

914
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:39,033
向下挖掘一会后

915
00:16:39,066 --> 00:16:39,966
我们发现了一个矿洞

916
00:16:39,966 --> 00:16:43,166
其中有着裸露的石墨矿

917
00:16:43,166 --> 00:16:44,266
我们挖了一些原矿

918
00:16:44,266 --> 00:16:46,666
将它们处理成纯净粉末

919
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:48,600
但它还粉碎得不够细

920
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:52,400
所以我们用新的手推磨将其磨得更细

921
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:54,600
再将其与高岭石粉和黏土混合

922
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:55,733
得到了耐火黏土

923
00:16:55,766 --> 00:16:58,000
我们可以将其捏成坩埚

924
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:00,200
和普通黏土一样

925
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:02,066
我们必须将它在放在木炭炉里烧制

926
00:17:02,100 --> 00:17:03,966
来制成陶器

927
00:17:03,966 --> 00:17:05,566
但经过很长时间后

928
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:08,000
我们意识到这样行不通

929
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,200
我们必须将其加热到黄白****(4)才行

930
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:14,333
然而我们的木炭最多只能烧到黄白**(2)

931
00:17:14,466 --> 00:17:17,000
一种解决方案是使用更好的燃料

932
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,466
比如我们在钻石石墨矿脉里收集到的煤炭

933
00:17:20,500 --> 00:17:22,400
但我们的存量很少

934
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:24,766
所以我们把它留下以备更好的用途

935
00:17:24,900 --> 00:17:26,966
取而代之的是，我们制作一种新工具

936
00:17:26,966 --> 00:17:30,766
从处理获取羊毛而留下的兽皮开始

937
00:17:30,866 --> 00:17:33,166
这些兽皮还太粗糙太脏

938
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,900
所以我们开始清洁

939
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,966
首先将其浸泡在石灰水中

940
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,233
接下来为了获得一张足够结实的桌子

941
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:41,666
我们放下一块原木并剥掉树皮

942
00:17:41,866 --> 00:17:44,066
现在我们可以把准备好的兽皮铺在上面

943
00:17:44,066 --> 00:17:46,366
开始进行刮制

944
00:17:46,366 --> 00:17:48,666
一旦我们完成了刮制皮革

945
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:50,600
我们将其封存在装有淡水的大桶里

946
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:52,633
清理掉所有残留

947
00:17:52,666 --> 00:17:55,666
最后再准备一些鞣酸

948
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,466
将预制皮革在其中浸泡来得到真正的皮革

949
00:17:58,466 --> 00:18:01,066
有了它，我们现在就可以合成我们的新工具

950
00:18:01,100 --> 00:18:03,400
来提高木炭炉温度

951
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,266
也就是风箱

952
00:18:04,366 --> 00:18:07,266
而这时我们才意识到已经入了冬季

953
00:18:07,266 --> 00:18:09,266
而我们的家还没有屋顶

954
00:18:09,266 --> 00:18:13,366

所以在用我们的新玩具来做出坩埚后


955
00:18:13,366 --> 00:18:15,366
我们很快也做好了屋顶

956
00:18:15,366 --> 00:18:19,200
这地方不仅冷到会产生冰溜子

957
00:18:19,200 --> 00:18:20,966
还很黑

958
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:24,000
然而火把在tfc里只能烧两天

959
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,600
我们可以塑形一个南瓜来做装饰

960
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:28,200
它还会让火把的燃烧时间加倍

961
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,900
但这仍然不够

962
00:18:29,900 --> 00:18:32,200
另一个不错的选择是灯

963
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:36,000
但大概只有第一次做的时候会觉得有趣

964
00:18:36,066 --> 00:18:40,466

第一步是在砧上制作灯的金属框架


965
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:42,300
随后我们需要玻璃

966
00:18:42,300 --> 00:18:44,000
我们准备了一种

967
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:46,866
由几种很容易获得的材料混合而成的混合物

968
00:18:46,866 --> 00:18:50,266
将混合物置于陶瓷吹风管上，再加热它

969
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:52,200
但刚拿出来时它还太热

970
00:18:52,266 --> 00:18:55,400
我们本能地将其丢掉了

971
00:18:55,400 --> 00:18:57,200
在使用第二根吹风管

972
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,266
来避免我们被前一根烫伤后

973
00:18:59,300 --> 00:19:04,966
我们开始琢磨如何操作我们的这些工具来完成玻璃

974
00:19:04,966 --> 00:19:05,866
照例

975
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:09,400
我们可以在群峦手册里找到说明

976
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:13,066
所以我们在一只手上拿吹风管

977
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:15,800
另一只手拿上带有熔融玻璃的热吹风管

978
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:16,733
交换主副手

979
00:19:16,766 --> 00:19:19,400
向吹风管内吹气

980
00:19:19,666 --> 00:19:20,966
接下来挤压它

981
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:25,366
在玻璃冷到无法继续处理之前

982
00:19:25,366 --> 00:19:27,566
我们将其放回木炭炉重新加热

983
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,233
一旦将其取出

984
00:19:29,266 --> 00:19:31,766
我们用压板挤压它，随后再次吹气

985
00:19:31,966 --> 00:19:35,800
最后，在我们切下处理完成的灯罩前

986
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,200
我们最后一次地加热它

987
00:19:38,466 --> 00:19:40,266
将灯罩和框架组合在一起后

988
00:19:40,266 --> 00:19:41,466
我们最终获得了灯

989
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:44,600
不过它仍然需要燃料

990
00:19:44,766 --> 00:19:47,466
为此我们可以用杂酚油

991
00:19:47,466 --> 00:19:50,666
通过管道从我们的新焦炉来供给它

992
00:19:50,900 --> 00:19:52,366
最后一件事就是

993
00:19:52,366 --> 00:19:54,933
用已经点燃了的火把点燃灯

994
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:57,633
有了这么一丝光明和初步的科技发展

995
00:19:57,666 --> 00:19:59,333
我们的火柴盒看起来焕然一新

996
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,800
虽然现在一切都好起来了

997
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,266
我们仍然需要面对不少问题

998
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:06,666
我们家旁边的湖正在封冻

999
00:20:06,766 --> 00:20:09,166
这使得水成为了一个问题

1000
00:20:09,266 --> 00:20:10,466
为了解决它

1001
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:11,900
我们做了一个铁水壶

1002
00:20:11,900 --> 00:20:14,766
这可以让我们把水带在身上

1003
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:17,966
我们用之前处理皮革剩下的水来填满水壶

1004
00:20:18,166 --> 00:20:21,600
现在我们可以随时随地喝上干净的水了

1005
00:20:21,766 --> 00:20:23,266
但除此之外

1006
00:20:23,266 --> 00:20:25,466
我们还需要更好的食物

1007
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:30,333
我们先把一些剩下的小麦磨成更细的粉末

1008
00:20:30,466 --> 00:20:34,166
随后我们加入水来做成面团

1009
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:37,400
在能更好地控制的烤架的帮助下

1010
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:39,366
我们做出了几条面包

1011
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:42,000
最后我们加入一些蔬菜和肉

1012
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:44,266
来做出一些美味的三明治

1013
00:20:44,366 --> 00:20:47,900
除此之外更加适合这个寒冷气候的食物是汤

1014
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:50,933
我们将陶锅架在火上并加入水

1015
00:20:50,966 --> 00:20:54,200
接着加入食材后将其煮沸

1016
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:55,233
一旦完成

1017
00:20:55,266 --> 00:20:56,666
我们用一些碗来盛汤

1018
00:20:56,666 --> 00:20:58,266
饱餐了一顿

1019
00:20:58,366 --> 00:20:59,666
现在我们唯一缺少的

1020
00:20:59,700 --> 00:21:02,800
是一个能装下这些新东西的更好办法

1021
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:04,400
为了能承担这些重量

1022
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:07,066
我们需要一些由坚固材料制成的东西

1023
00:21:07,066 --> 00:21:08,600
比如黄麻纤维

1024
00:21:08,866 --> 00:21:11,200
我们可以将它制成粗麻布

1025
00:21:11,200 --> 00:21:13,800
有了它，我们现在可以做一个背包

1026
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:17,733
而现在我们就可以随身带着砧

1027
00:21:17,766 --> 00:21:19,566
同时也不会拖慢我们的速度

1028
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:21,700
这个背包也将成为

1029
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:23,700
我们收集更多铁矿时的好朋友

1030
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:25,400
不过那是下一集的故事了

1031
00:21:25,566 --> 00:21:27,066
下次见

1032
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:28,200
拜拜

